<script>
// Get the modal
var modal = document.getElementById('myModal');

// Get the <span> element that closes the modal
var span = document.getElementsByClassName("close")[0];

// When the user clicks on <span> (x), close the modal
span.onclick = function() {
    modal.style.display = "none";
}

// When the user clicks anywhere outside of the modal, close it
window.onclick = function(event) {
    if (event.target == modal) {
        modal.style.display = "none";
    }
}
</script>

    <h3>The Team</h3>
    <p>Team Velox Rota (TVR) is made up of passionate athletes from around the U.S. participating in events ranging from multi-day endurance cycling events to racing up skyscrapers. Our Members unite through the common threads of fitness, helping others, and having a good time along the way! Since its origin in 2005 when TVR was purely a cycling team and consisted of 18 riders, the team has exploded in size and success. With the consistent help of our personal donors, and team sponsors, we have raised over $1 million dollars, one of 3 teams in Greater New England area!</p>

    <h3>The Cause</h3>
    <p>Multiple Sclerosis (MS) is the most widespread, unpredictable, disabling neurological disease of the central nervous system that does not currently have a cure. MS interrupts the flow of information within the brain and parts of the body with symptoms ranging in severity from numbness in limbs to paralysis.  You can develop MS at any age, but most people are diagnosed between the ages of 20 and 40. There are relapsing and remitting types of MS and progressive types, but the course is rarely predictable.  Researchers still donâ€™t fully understand the causes of MS or why the rate of progression is so difficult to determine.The Multiple Sclerosis Foundation estimates that more than 400,000 people in the United States and about 2.5 million people around the world have MS. About 200 new cases are diagnosed each week in the United States. MS affects more than 22,000 people in Connecticut, Maine, Massachusetts, New Hampshire, Rhode Island & Vermont.   
    </p>
    <p>For more information about MS, click here: 
      <a href="http://www.healthline.com/health/multiple-sclerosis/facts-statistics-infographic" target="_blank">
	<img width="20" class="fight_ms_logo" src="@routes.Assets.at("images/fight_ms.png")"/>
      </a>
    </p>

